value.value: 均衡性小人症
abnormally undersized with both limbs and trunk symmetrically shorter; usually due to chemical, endocrine, nutritional or nonosseous influences

definition.value: In humans, dwarfism is defined as a condition in which the standing height of a person is below the third percentile.

value.value: 雄の受精能遅延
ability of a male organism to produce live offspring occurring at a later than expected age
雌の受精能遅延
ability of a female organism to produce live offspring occurring at a later than expected age
膣サイズの異常
anomaly in the size of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva
膣重量の異常
anomaly in the weight of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva
膣重量の増加
increase in the weight of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva
膣重量の減少
decrease in the weight of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva
膣肥大
increase in the size of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva
膣の過形成
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the vagina, typically resulting in increased size
膣の矮小化
decrease in the size of the female reproductive canal located between the uterus and the vulva
膣の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the vagina, typically resulting in decreased size
四肢一側形成不全症
congenital absence of part of an extremity, such as absent fibula with the tibia present
肝実質の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the functional units of the liver including the lobules
肝小葉の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the polygonal structure of the liver that consists of hepatocytes radiating outward from a hepatic vein

definition.value: Do not confuse this term with the anatomic lobes of the liver.

value.value: 肝類洞周囲腔の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the extravascular space in the liver between the parenchymal cells and a sinusoid that contains the blood plasma
肝類洞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the hepatic distensible vascular blood channels lined with highly fenestrated endothelial cells that function to exchange fluids, nutrients, proteins and wastes
類洞周囲脂質細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the fat-storing cells that line the hepatic sinusoids
毛細胆管形態異常
any structural anomaly of the intercellular channels that take up bile from hepatocytes and transport it to the bile ducts
門脈小葉の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the triangular region on the periphery of the liver lobules that contain a bile duct and a terminal branch of the hepatic artery and portal vein, and may also include a lymphatic vessel
門脈３分岐の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the three vessels of the portal lobule including the bile duct, a terminal branch of the hepatic artery and portal vein, and may also include a lymphatic vessel
膣の早期開口
the opening of the genital canal in a female occurs at an earlier than expected age
生殖能力の早期老化現象
loss of reproductive capacity occurring at an earlier than expected age
血中浸透圧異常
anomaly in the concentration of ions in the blood or blood fractions compared to the normal state, sometimes reported as increased or decreased osmotic fragility
血液モル浸透圧の増加
increase in the concentration of ions in the blood compared to the normal state
血液モル浸透圧の減少
decrease in the concentration of ions in the blood compared to the normal state
肛門の欠如
absence of the lower opening of the digestive tract
盲腸の欠如
absence of the large sac at the ileum and large intestine junction
母趾の欠如
absence of the first or primary digit of the foot
毛髪再生の早期化
faster initiation of the hair growth cycle (anagen) after catagen phase
感覚毛数異常
any anomaly in the number of the stiff hairs projecting from the face around the nose of most mammals which act as touch receptors
進行性脱毛症
thinning of hair (coat) over time, usually in a defined pattern, until entirely gone with no recurrent growth

label.value: abnormal sesamoid bone of gastrocnemius morphology

value.value: 腓腹筋種子骨の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal sesamoid bone of gastrocnemius morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the small sesamoid bones situated behind the condyles of the femur
性周期の延長
increase in the length of the estrous cycle
性周期の短縮
decrease in the length of the estrous cycle
性周期の遅延
onset of the estrous cycle of females occurring at a later than expected age

definition.value: This term should only be used to annotate a delay in the onset of the first estrous cycle in female animals.

value.value: 発情間期の欠如
failure of female animals to enter or progress through the estrous cycle
発情間期の異常

any anomaly or aberrant timing of the last phase of the estrous cycle, during which unfertilized eggs are eliminated, the vagina and vulva are at a minimum size, and new follicles begin to undergo a rapid growth for the next ovulation; if pregnancy does not occur, the metestrous phase is ultimately followed by the diestrous phase
発情間期の延長
increase in the length of the diestrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
発情間期の短縮
decrease in the length of the diestrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
発情前期の異常

any anomaly or aberrant timing of the first phase of the estrous cycle which begins when a new batch of eggs reach maturity within ovarian follicles that are ripe and large; external examination of the female usually shows a bloated vulva with an open vagina
発情前期の延長
increase in the length of the proestrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
発情前期の短縮
decrease in the length of the proestrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
発情期の異常

any anomaly or aberrant timing of the phase of the estrous cycle which begins with the ovulation of fully mature oocytes and during which the vulva remains in an extended state with an open vagina, and females are maximally receptive to male advances
発情期の延長
increase in the length of the estrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
発情期の短縮
decrease in the length of the estrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
発情後期の異常

any anomaly or aberrant timing of the phase of the estrous cycle which follows estrus when mature eggs move through the oviducts and into the uterus; the vulva is no longer bloated, and the vagina is now closed
発情後期の延長
increase in the length of the metestrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
発情期の欠如
absence or failure of the estrous phase of the estrous cycle in female animals
脳髄膜形態異常
any structural anomaly in any of the membranes covering the brain, including the dura mater (external), arachnoid (middle), and pia mater (internal)
脊髄髄膜の形態異常
any structural anomaly in any of the membranes covering the spinal cord, including the dura mater (external), arachnoid (middle), and pia mater (internal)
